                        "steps":  [
                                      "Before turning on the wok, break up any clumps in the cold rice with your hands or a spoon. Stir the soy sauce and oyster sauce together in a small bowl so the sauce is ready when the wok is hot.",
                                      "Season the diced chicken lightly with salt and pepper. Heat a wok or large skillet over high heat until a drop of water sizzles quickly, then add 1 tablespoon oil.",
                                      "Add the chicken in a single layer and let it sear for about 1 minute before stirring. Stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes, until the pieces are browned in spots and cooked through, then move them to a plate.",
                                      "Lower the heat to medium-high, add 1 teaspoon oil if the wok looks dry, and pour in the beaten eggs. Scramble just until softly set, about 30 to 60 seconds, then move the eggs to the plate with the chicken.",
                                      "Return the wok to high heat and add the remaining oil. Add the scallion whites, garlic, and ginger and stir for 20 to 30 seconds, just until fragrant but not browned.",
                                      "Add the frozen vegetables straight from the bag and stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes, until hot and the extra moisture has mostly cooked off. The wok should sound lively, not watery.",
                                      "Add the cold rice and spread it across the hot surface. Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes, pressing and tossing to heat it through and lightly toast some grains.",
                                      "Return the chicken and eggs to the wok. Pour the sauce around the edges, toss everything together for 1 to 2 minutes, and watch for the rice to look evenly seasoned instead of wet.",
                                      "Turn off the heat and stir in the sesame oil and scallion greens. Taste and adjust with a small splash of soy sauce if needed, then serve hot."
                                  ],
